| Overview            = The Super-Skrulls are the elite shock troops, infiltrators, and special operatives of the Skrull Empire. Super soldiers who have been given super powers, usually those of Earth's heroes but also that of other aliens (e.g. [[Imperial Guard|Shi'ar Imperial Guard]] or the [[Norrin Radd (Earth-616)|Silver Surfer]]).{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 249|250}}{{r|X-Men Vol 2 89|90}}{{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 13|14}}{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} Originally their powers were technological in nature (e.g. cybernetic implants) which simulated those powers, but eventually the Skrulls were able to give the Super-Skrulls those super powers at the genetic level.{{r|X-Men Vol 2 95}}{{r|New Avengers Vol 1 44}}{{r|Deadpool Vol 4 2|3}} Super-Skrulls can be Skrull warriors who volunteered to undergo the enhancement to become Super-Skrulls.{{r|Fantastic Four #18}}{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 358}} They can also be lab-grown clones who were "born" as Super-Skrulls.{{r|Deadpool Vol 4 2|3}} 

The Skrull Empire deploys the Super-Skrulls individually or in squadrons that can be dozens strong.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} Assignments given to Super-Skrulls have included protecting Skrull worlds,{{r|U.S.Avengers Vol 1 11|12}} serving as front-line combat shock troops,{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} as doppelgangers of superheroes,{{r|Fantastic Four Vol 1 249|250}}{{r|Silver Surfer Vol 3 13|14}} or as sleeper agents.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1}} The size of the Super-Skrull force is unknown but in the Skrull invasion of Earth, thousands of Super-Skrulls were deployed in New York City alone{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 5}}. Super-Skrulls are trained at special facilities, such as the "War-Moon" orbiting Tarnax IV which was destroyed along with the throneworld by [[Galan (Earth-616)|Galactus]] and the multiple training centers on [[Tarnax VII]] which were destroyed by the Kree [[Va-Sohn (Earth-616)|Starbrand]] a decade after the invasion of Earth.{{r|X-Men Vol 2 90}}{{r|Starbrand & Nightmask Vol 1 6}}

| HistoryText             = The Skrull warrior (and future emperor) [[Kl'rt (Earth-616)|Kl'rt the Super-Skrull]] was the first Super-Skrull, the original and greatest of all the Super-Skrulls. He was given technological enhancements to simulate the powers of the Fantastic Four. Kl'rt was sent to conquer Earth and ended up being more than a match for the Fantastic Four but ultimately failed in his mission.{{r|Fantastic Four #18}}

In the aftermath of the [[Kree-Skrull War]], several of Earth's greatest super heroes who recently formed the [[Illuminati (Earth-616)|Illuminati]] went to the [[Tarnax IV|Skrull throneworld]] to warn the Skrulls to stay away from Earth. The heroes were captured and confined by the Skrulls who tortured them, downloaded from their brains all their knowledge, and took their DNA samples.{{r|New Avengers: Illuminati Vol 1 1}}{{r|New Avengers Vol 1 40}}

The Chief Scientist [[Granok (Earth-616)|Granok]] in his attempt to recreate the lost gene of the [[Warskrulls]] experimented on [[Skrull Mutants]], and used the gained knowledge to create a comprehensive personality matrix which allowed infiltrators to survive even genetic testing and telepathic examination.{{r|X-Men Vol 2 95}} The Head Priest of the Sciences, [[Dro'ge Fenu Edu (Earth-616)|Dro'ge]] would use Granok's research to perfect the Super-Skrull program. He discovered how to manipulate the DNA samples they took from the Illuminati to create improved Super-Skrulls.{{r|New Avengers Vol 1 44}} Using science and magic they created Super-Skrulls that were imbued with the memories and powers of the subjects and could not be detected by technology, magic, telepathy, or various superhuman senses.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1}}

During the invasion of Earth, the Skrulls deployed thousands of Super-Skrulls which did battle with Earth's defenders in orbit, the [[Moon]] and various locations across Earth (e.g. [[New York City]], the [[Savage Land]], [[Israel]], [[Wakanda]], and [[San Francisco]]).{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1|8}} The greatest concentration of Super-Skrulls were in New York City in which a ground assault force of thousands of Super-Skrulls were used.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 1}}{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 5}} The [[Project P.E.G.A.S.U.S. Facility]] was attacked by over a hundred Super-Skrulls and in [[Camp Hammond]] were dozens of Super-Skrulls who had infiltrated the [[Initiative]] program.{{r|Nova Vol 4 18}}{{r|Avengers: The Initiative Vol 1 14}} In the final battle in New York, the Super-Skrulls deployed hundreds of Super-Skrulls.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 6|7}}

Despite the losses suffered at Earth, the Super-Skrull program continues to be active under the rule of Kl'rt the original Super-Skrull. Various Super-Skrull training centers exist in the empire.{{r|Starbrand & Nightmask Vol 1 6}} Super-Skrulls have also been assigned to Skrull worlds as enforcers or protectors.{{r|U.S.Avengers Vol 1 11|12}} 

==Known Super-Skrulls==
Besides [[Kl'rt (Earth-616)|Super-Skrull]], [[Paibok (Earth-616)|Power-Skrull]] and [[Xavin (Earth-616)|Xavin]], among the Super-Skrulls are:

===Empress R'klll===
The duplicitous [[R'Klll (Earth-616)|R'Klll]], long thought to've perished in the destruction of [[Tarnax IV]]. Had secretly undergone a type of Power Skrull enhancement process which enables her to mask her DNA code from even the most thorough of genetic scanning devices.{{r|Empyre: Aftermath Avengers Vol 1 1}} Enabling her to take the form of anyone or everyone and mimic their genetic signatures right down to the biomolecular level.{{r|Empyre Vol 1 4}}

===Ani-Men Super-Skrull===
The [[Ani-Men (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Ani-Men Skrull]] is a Super-Skrull that has the powers of the [[Ani-Men (Earth-616)|Ani-Men]].{{r|New Warriors Vol 4 14}}

===Asgardian Mix Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking Wakanda had [[Loki Laufeyson (Earth-616)|Loki]]'s powers and wielded technological copies of both [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]]'s [[Mjolnir]] and [[Beta Ray Bill (Earth-616)|Beta Ray Bill]]'s [[Stormbreaker]]. He also has Loki's helmet horns on his head. After [[T'Challa (Earth-616)|Black Panther]] defeated the Luke Cage-Skinned Skrull, the Asgardian-Mix Skrull attacked Black Panther alongside the Powerhouse-Mix Skrull. He was beheaded by Black Panther.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 40}}

===Avengers Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking London had all the powers of original Avengers members [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Ant-Man]], [[Bruce Banner (Earth-616)|Hulk]], [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]], [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]], and [[Janet Van Dyne (Earth-616)|Wasp]]. His hybrid appearance gave him a copy of the head and torso of the [[Iron Man Armor Model 1]], Thor's arms and legs, and Wasp's wings.{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 1|4}}

===Champions Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking London had the powers of the [[Champions of Los Angeles (Earth-616)|Champions]] members [[Warren Worthington III (Earth-616)|Angel]], [[Johnathon Blaze (Earth-616)|Ghost Rider]], and [[Robert Drake (Earth-616)|Iceman]]. His hybrid appearance gave him Ghost Rider's head, Angel's wings, and Iceman's left arm. [[Brian Braddock (Earth-616)|Captain Britain]] tricked it into freezing it's head so that he could break it.{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 1}}

===Criti Noll===
The first [[Criti Noll (Earth-616)|Criti Noll]] has the powers of [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Yellowjacket]]. She was reluctant to follow the Invasion plans and was killed by the [[Timothy Dugan (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Dum Dum Dugan Skrull]].{{r|Mighty Avengers Vol 1 15|17}}

Veranke created a [[Criti Noll (Clone) (Earth-616)|clone of Criti Noll]] who posed as Hank Pym. She not only had Hank Pym's powers, but also the powers of [[T'Challa (Earth-616)|Black Panther]], [[Pietro Maximoff (Earth-616)|Quicksilver]], and [[Vision (Earth-616)|Vision]].{{r|Mighty Avengers Vol 1 17}}

===Defenders Super-Skrull===
One of the Super-Skrulls attacking London possessed the powers of [[Defenders (Earth-616)|Defenders]] members [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]] and [[Norrin Radd (Earth-616)|Silver Surfer]]. His hybrid appearance gave him Namor's ankle wings and Silver Surfer's skin. This Skrull was killed by [[Jacqueline Falsworth (Earth-616)|Spitfire]].{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 1}}

===Godkiller Super-Skrull===
The [[Godkiller (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Godkiller]] is a specially-bred Super-Skrull that has the powers of [[Anita Ehren (Earth-616)|Battleaxe]], [[Thundra (Earth-715)|Thundra]], [[Mary MacPherran (Earth-616)|Titania]], and [[Marsha Rosenberg (Earth-616)|Volcana]]. She was also bred to wield [[Stormbreaker]].{{r|Secret Invasion: Thor Vol 1 2}}

===Hydra Prime 001===
[[Hydra Prime 001 (Earth-616)|Hydra Prime 001]] is a special Super-Skrull that displayed cryokinesis, a healing factor, flight, claws, optic blasts, fire breath, and super strength.{{r|Ms. Marvel Vol 2 30}}

===Illuminati Super-Skrull===
The [[Illuminati (Earth-616)|Illuminati]] Skrull was the first of many, having the super powers of [[Blackagar Boltagon (Earth-616)|Black Bolt]] (whom he was posing as), [[Stephen Strange (Earth-616)|Doctor Strange]], [[Reed Richards (Earth-616)|Mister Fantastic]], [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]] and [[Charles Xavier (Earth-616)|Professor X]]. This [[Blackagar Boltagon (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Skrull]] revealed himself when [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] brought back the group one last time, to talk about the Skrull posing as [[Elektra Natchios (Earth-616)|Elektra]]. As they discussed what to do with the body, the Illuminati Super-Skrull revealed himself and attacked. The Illuminati Super-Skrull was killed by Namor, whom twisted his neck, by stabbing him on a piece of rubble.{{r|New Avengers: Illuminati Vol 2 5}}

One Illuminati Super-Skrull variation partaking in the first invasion was shown to have a copy of Doctor Strange's [[Cloak of Levitation]], copies of Iron Man's left arm and arc reactor, Black Bolt's body, and Mister Fantastic's elasticity.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 2}}

Another Illuminati Super-Skrull was seen in the invasion of New York and was decapitated by [[Lily Hollister (Earth-616)|Menace]].{{r|Secret Invasion: The Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 2}}

===Inhumans Super-Skrull===
The [[Inhumans (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Inhuman Super-Skrull]] partook in the attack on [[Attilan]] and has the powers of the [[House of Agon|Inhuman Royal Family]]. It's hybrid appearance gave him [[Medusalith Amaquelin (Earth-616)|Medusa]]'s hair and [[Gorgon Petragon (Earth-616)|Gorgon]]'s hooves.{{r|Secret Invasion: Inhumans Vol 1 1}}

===Luke Cage-Skinned Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls that attacked [[Wakanda]] not only had [[Luke Cage (Earth-616)|Luke Cage]]'s skin, it also had [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Wolverine]]'s claws, [[Daniel Rand (Earth-616)|Iron Fist]]'s "iron fist" move, [[Bullseye (Lester) (Earth-616)|Bullseye]]'s aim, and the fighting styles of [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]], [[Marc Spector (Earth-616)|Moon Knight]], [[Shang-Chi (Earth-616)|Shang-Chi]], [[Matthew Murdock (Earth-616)|Daredevil]], [[Elektra Natchios (Earth-616)|Elektra]], and [[T'Challa (Earth-616)|Black Panther]]. His hybrid appearance gave him with Luke Cage's muscular appearance, Bullseye's target symbol on his forehead, and Wolverine's claws on his hands while his left hand performs the "iron fist" move. This Skrull faced Black Panther on the battlefield.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 39}} As he fought it, Black Panther noted it's abilities. After mentioning Bullseye's accuracy and the combined fighting abilities of some of the mentioned heroes, the Luke Cage-Skinned Super-Skrull continued it's battle. Black Panther noticed that he can't use all his powers at once. Black Panther defeated it by breaking his left arm, ripping out his left eye, breaking his left leg. Black Panther gave him the option to rot on the ground or crawl back to his masters to show what he did to him.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 40}}

===Mystic Super-Skrull===
The four-armed Mystic Super-Skrull that led the invasion on Britain has the powers and abilities of [[Stephen Strange (Earth-616)|Doctor Strange]], [[Dormammu (Earth-616)|Dormammu]], and [[Loki Laufeyson (Earth-616)|Loki]]. His hybrid appearance gave him with Doctor Strange's outfit, Dormammu's head, and Loki's helmet horns. After a fierce battle, a revived Captain Britain beheaded the Mystic Skrull.{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 2|4}}

===New Warriors Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking the New Warriors had the powers of the original founders of the New Warriors [[Angelica Jones (Earth-616)|Firestar]], [[Vance Astrovik (Earth-616)|Justice]], [[Namorita Prentiss (Earth-616)|Namorita]], [[Dwayne Taylor (Earth-616)|Night Thrasher]], [[Richard Rider (Earth-616)|Nova]], and [[Robert Baldwin (Earth-616)|Speedball]].{{r|New Avengers Vol 4 15}}

===Powerhouse Mix Super-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking Wakanda had the combined strengths of [[Bruce Banner (Earth-616)|Hulk]], [[Cain Marko (Earth-616)|Juggernaut]], and [[Benjamin Grimm (Earth-616)|Thing]]. His hybrid appearance gave him Juggernaut's head, body, and legs, Hulk's left arm, and Thing's right arm. After Black Panther defeated the Luke Cage-Skinned Skrull, the Powerhouse Mix Skrull attacked Black Panther alongside the Asgardian Mix Super-Skrull where the Powerhouse Mix Super-Skrull considered the defeated Skrull as a warm-up for Black Panther's battle with them.{{r|Black Panther Vol 4 40}}

===[[Sinister Six (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Sinister Six Skrull]]===
This Super-Skrull had the powers of the Sinister Six members [[Aleksei Sytsevich (Earth-616)|Rhino]], [[Edward Brock (Earth-616)|Venom]]. [[Curtis Connors (Earth-616)|Lizard]], [[Maxwell Dillon (Earth-616)|Electro]], [[Morris Bench (Earth-616)|Hydro-Man]], and [[William Baker (Earth-616)|Sandman]]. His hybrid appearance showed him with the head mask of Rhino, the body of Venom, and the tail of Lizard. The Sinister Six Skrull posed as Spider-Man to find the real Spider-Man where he fought [[Alana Jobson (Earth-616)|Jackpot]] who managed to kill him.{{r|Secret Invasion: The Amazing Spider-Man Vol 1 1}}

===Squadron Supreme-Skrull===
One of the Skrulls attacking London possessed the powers of [[Squadron Supreme (Earth-712)|Squadron Supreme]] members [[Mark Milton (Earth-712)|Hyperion]] and [[Stanley Stewart (Earth-712)|Whizzer]] while wielding a copy of [[Joseph Ledger (Earth-712)|Doctor Spectrum]]'s [[Power Prism]]. His hybrid appearance had him sporting a combination of Hyperion's outfit and Doctor Spectrum's outfit. This Skrull was beheaded by Captain Britain.{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 1|4}}

===Thor Super-Skrull===
The Thor-Skrull appeared along with the X-Skrull after Namor slew the Illuminati-Skrull. This Skrull wielded a technological copy of Mjolnir. It was killed by an explosion set off by Iron Man.{{r|New Avengers: Illuminati Vol 2 5}}

The Thor-Skrull carried a hammer resembling [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]]'s hammer, [[Mjolnir]].

===Thunderbolts Super-Skrull===
A Super-Skrull that attacked [[Melissa Gold (Earth-616)|Songbird]] not only had her powers, but also had the powers of [[Erik Josten (Earth-616)|Atlas]].{{r|Thunderbolts Vol 1 123}}

===X-Skrull===
The X-Skrulls are the type of Super-Skrull that have the powers of the [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]]. There have been two X-Men Skrulls, both appearing to have [[James Howlett (Earth-616)|Wolverine]], [[Piotr Rasputin (Earth-616)|Colossus]], [[Kurt Wagner (Earth-616)|Nightcrawler]], and [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]]' powers. One X-Skrull attacked the Illuminati alongside the Thor Skrull.{{r|New Avengers: Illuminati Vol 2 5}} [[Rl'nnd]] is the first example of the X-Skrull.{{r|Ms. Marvel Vol 2 25}} Some of the X-Skrulls that sport Wolverine's powers also wore his head mask that was amalgamated with [[Cyclops' Visor]].{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 2}}{{r|Secret Invasion: X-Men Vol 1 2}}

A version of an X-Skrull that fought the New Warriors had the powers of the original X-Men [[Warren Worthington III (Earth-616)|Angel]], [[Henry McCoy (Earth-616)|Beast]], [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]], [[Robert Drake (Earth-616)|Iceman]], and [[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|Jean Grey]].{{r|New Warriors Vol 4 15}}

One X-Skrull who had the powers of Colossus, Cyclops, and Wolverine took part in the invasion of Attilan.{{r|Secret Invasion: Inhumans Vol 1 2}}

During the invasion of San Francisco, numerous X-Skrulls were unleashed. There is an X-Skrull who has the powers of Cyclops, an X-Skrull who has the powers of [[Roberto Da Costa (Earth-616)|Sunspot]], and an X-Skrull who has the powers of Wolverine.{{r|Secret Invasion: X-Men Vol 1 1}} There is an X-Skrull who has the powers of [[Katherine Pryde (Earth-616)|Shadowcat]] and an X-Skrull who has the powers of Colossus, Cyclops, Iceman, and Wolverine,{{r|Secret Invasion: X-Men Vol 1 2}} The X-Skrulls are shown to be vulnerable to the [[Legacy Virus]].{{r|Secret Invasion: X-Men Vol 1 4}}

===Unnamed Super-Skrulls===
There are thousands of other Super-Skrulls that have not been part of just one team. Many Skrulls appear to be modeled only after one character including [[Warren Worthington III (Earth-616)|Archangel]], [[Max Eisenhardt (Earth-616)|Magneto]], [[Thor Odinson (Earth-616)|Thor]], [[MacDonald Gargan (Earth-616)|Venom]], and many others including even [[Galan (Earth-616)|Galactus]]. There are some Super-Skrulls that resemble hybrids of other characters like a [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]]/[[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] Super-Skrull and a [[Otto Octavius (Earth-616)|Doctor Octopus]]/[[Maxwell Dillon (Earth-616)|Electro]]/[[William Baker (Earth-616)|Sandman]] Super-Skrull.{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 5}}{{r|Secret Invasion Vol 1 2}}

Here are descriptions of the other unnamed Skrulls:

* There was a Super-Skrull posing as [[Matthew Murdock (Skrull) (Earth-616)|Daredevil]] that was sent to take out [[Maya Lopez (Earth-616)|Echo]]. She appeared to have the powers of Cyclops, Nightcrawler, and [[Jonathan Storm (Earth-616)|Human Torch]].{{r|New Avengers Vol 1 39}}
* A [[Henry Pym (Giant-Man Skrull) (Earth-616)|Super-Skrull that has the powers of]] [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Giant-Man]].{{r|Ms. Marvel Vol 2 28}}
* One Super-Skrull has the powers of [[Medusalith Amaquelin (Earth-616)|Medusa]] and [[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|White Phoenix]].{{r|Secret Invasion: Inhumans Vol 1 2|4}}
* One of the Skrulls attacking London possessed [[Michael Morbius (Earth-616)|Morbius the Living Vampire]]' vampiric abilities.{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 1}}
* An assortment of Skrulls attacked [[Otherworld]]. They consist of an [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]]/[[Otto Octavius (Earth-616)|Doctor Octopus]] Skrull, an [[Ultron (Earth-616)|Ultron]] Skrull, an Iron Man/[[Norbert Ebersol (Earth-616)|Fixer]] Skrull that beheaded the [[Bercilak de Hautdesert (Earth-616)|Green Knight]].{{r|Captain Britain and MI-13 Vol 1 2}}
* A [[Bruce Banner (Skrull) (Earth-616)|"World War Hulk"]] Super-Skrull that had the appearance of [[Bruce Banner (Earth-616)|Hulk]]'s Sakaaran appearance where it had Hulk's strength and the optic blasts of Cyclops.{{r|Ms. Marvel Vol 2 28}}
* An assortment of Super-Skrulls took part in the invasion of Attilan. They consist of a Super-Skrull with the powers of [[Johnathon Blaze (Earth-616)|Ghost Rider]], a [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]]/[[Peter Parker (Earth-616)|Spider-Man]] Super-Skrull, a Super-Skrull that has the powers of [[Henry Pym (Earth-616)|Ant-Man]], and a Super-Skrull who has the powers of [[Reed Richards (Earth-616)|Mister Fantastic]] and Medusa.{{r|Secret Invasion: Inhumans Vol 1 2}}

